==English==
===Etymology===
OE. [[agreven]], OF. [[agrever]]; a (Latin ad) + grever to burden, injure, Latin gravare to weigh down, fr. gravis heavy.  See [[Grieve]], and compare with [[Aggravate]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈgɹiv/

===Verb (transitive)===
# To give pain or sorrow to; to afflict; hence, to oppress or injure in one's rights; to bear heavily upon;&mdash;now commonly  used in the passive TO be aggrieved.

===Verb (intransitive)===
#To [[grieve]]; to [[lament]].